{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Have you ever wondered"},{"time":2000,"text":"what is inside your dental plaque?"},{"time":5000,"text":"Probably not, but people like me do."},{"time":7000,"text":"I'm an archeological geneticist"},{"time":9000,"text":"at the Center for Evolutionary Medicine"},{"time":11000,"text":"at the University of Zurich,"},{"time":13000,"text":"and I study the origins and evolution of human health and disease"},{"time":16000,"text":"by conducting genetic research"},{"time":18000,"text":"on the skeletal and mummified remains of ancient humans."},{"time":21000,"text":"And through this work, I hope to better understand"},{"time":24000,"text":"the evolutionary vulnerabilities of our bodies,"},{"time":26000,"text":"so that we can improve"},{"time":29000,"text":"and better manage our health in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31000,"text":"There are different ways to approach evolutionary medicine,"},{"time":34000,"text":"and one way is to extract human DNA"},{"time":36000,"text":"from ancient bones."},{"time":38000,"text":"And from these extracts,"},{"time":40000,"text":"we can reconstruct the human genome at different points in time"},{"time":43000,"text":"and look for changes that might be related to adaptations,"},{"time":46000,"text":"risk factors and inherited diseases."},{"time":49000,"text":"But this is only one half of the story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52000,"text":"The most important health challenges today"},{"time":55000,"text":"are not caused by simple mutations in our genome,"},{"time":58000,"text":"but rather result from a complex and dynamic interplay"},{"time":61000,"text":"between genetic variation,"},{"time":63000,"text":"diet, microbes and parasites"},{"time":65000,"text":"and our immune response."},{"time":67000,"text":"All of these diseases"},{"time":69000,"text":"have a strong evolutionary component"},{"time":71000,"text":"that directly relates to the fact"},{"time":73000,"text":"that we live today in a very different environment"},{"time":75000,"text":"than the ones in which our bodies evolved."},{"time":78000,"text":"And in order to understand these diseases,"},{"time":80000,"text":"we need to move past studies of the human genome alone"},{"time":83000,"text":"and towards a more holistic approach"},{"time":85000,"text":"to human health in the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"But there are a lot of challenges for this."},{"time":89000,"text":"And first of all, what do we even study?"},{"time":92000,"text":"Skeletons are ubiquitous; they're found all over the place."},{"time":95000,"text":"But of course, all of the soft tissue has decomposed,"},{"time":98000,"text":"and the skeleton itself"},{"time":100000,"text":"has limited health information."},{"time":102000,"text":"Mummies are a great source of information,"},{"time":104000,"text":"except that they're really geographically limited"},{"time":107000,"text":"and limited in time as well."},{"time":109000,"text":"Coprolites are fossilized human feces,"},{"time":112000,"text":"and they're actually extremely interesting."},{"time":114000,"text":"You can learn a lot about ancient diet and intestinal disease,"},{"time":117000,"text":"but they are very rare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"So to address this problem,"},{"time":124000,"text":"I put together a team of international researchers"},{"time":126000,"text":"in Switzerland, Denmark and the U.K."},{"time":128000,"text":"to study a very poorly studied, little known material"},{"time":134000,"text":"that's found on people everywhere."},{"time":136000,"text":"It's a type of fossilized dental plaque"},{"time":139000,"text":"that is called officially dental calculus."},{"time":142000,"text":"Many of you may know it by the term tartar."},{"time":144000,"text":"It's what the dentist cleans off your teeth"},{"time":146000,"text":"every time that you go in for a visit."},{"time":148000,"text":"And in a typical dentistry visit,"},{"time":150000,"text":"you may have about 15 to 30 milligrams removed."},{"time":153000,"text":"But in ancient times before tooth brushing,"},{"time":156000,"text":"up to 600 milligrams might have built up on the teeth"},{"time":159000,"text":"over a lifetime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"And what's really important about dental calculus"},{"time":164000,"text":"is that it fossilizes just like the rest of the skeleton,"},{"time":167000,"text":"it's abundant in quantity before the present day"},{"time":170000,"text":"and it's ubiquitous worldwide."},{"time":172000,"text":"We find it in every population around the world at all time periods"},{"time":175000,"text":"going back tens of thousands of years."},{"time":177000,"text":"And we even find it in neanderthals and animals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180000,"text":"And so previous studies"},{"time":182000,"text":"had only focused on microscopy."},{"time":184000,"text":"They'd looked at dental calculus under a microscope,"},{"time":186000,"text":"and what they had found was things like pollen"},{"time":189000,"text":"and plant starches,"},{"time":191000,"text":"and they'd found muscle cells from animal meats"},{"time":193000,"text":"and bacteria."},{"time":195000,"text":"And so what my team of researchers, what we wanted to do,"},{"time":198000,"text":"is say, can we apply"},{"time":200000,"text":"genetic and proteomic technology"},{"time":202000,"text":"to go after DNA and proteins,"},{"time":204000,"text":"and from this can we get better taxonomic resolution"},{"time":207000,"text":"to really understand what's going on?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"And what we found"},{"time":211000,"text":"is that we can find many commensal and pathogenic bacteria"},{"time":213000,"text":"that inhabited the nasal passages and mouth."},{"time":216000,"text":"We also have found immune proteins"},{"time":219000,"text":"related to infection and inflammation"},{"time":222000,"text":"and proteins and DNA related to diet."},{"time":225000,"text":"But what was surprising to us, and also quite exciting,"},{"time":228000,"text":"is we also found bacteria"},{"time":230000,"text":"that normally inhabit upper respiratory systems."},{"time":232000,"text":"So it gives us virtual access to the lungs,"},{"time":235000,"text":"which is where many important diseases reside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238000,"text":"And we also found bacteria"},{"time":240000,"text":"that normally inhabit the gut."},{"time":242000,"text":"And so we can also now virtually gain access"},{"time":245000,"text":"to this even more distant organ system"},{"time":247000,"text":"that, from the skeleton alone,"},{"time":249000,"text":"has long decomposed."},{"time":251000,"text":"And so by applying ancient DNA sequencing"},{"time":253000,"text":"and protein mass spectrometry technologies"},{"time":255000,"text":"to ancient dental calculus,"},{"time":257000,"text":"we can generate immense quantities of data"},{"time":260000,"text":"that then we can use to begin to reconstruct a detailed picture"},{"time":263000,"text":"of the dynamic interplay"},{"time":265000,"text":"between diet, infection and immunity"},{"time":267000,"text":"thousands of years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269000,"text":"So what started out as an idea,"},{"time":271000,"text":"is now being implemented"},{"time":273000,"text":"to churn out millions of sequences"},{"time":275000,"text":"that we can use to investigate"},{"time":277000,"text":"the long-term evolutionary history of human health and disease,"},{"time":280000,"text":"right down to the genetic code of individual pathogens."},{"time":283000,"text":"And from this information"},{"time":285000,"text":"we can learn about how pathogens evolve"},{"time":287000,"text":"and also why they continue to make us sick."},{"time":290000,"text":"And I hope I have convinced you"},{"time":292000,"text":"of the value of dental calculus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294000,"text":"And as a final parting thought,"},{"time":296000,"text":"on behalf of future archeologists,"},{"time":299000,"text":"I would like to ask you to please think twice"},{"time":302000,"text":"before you go home and brush your teeth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":306000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}